            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1422042521,
            "creation_date": 1422042521,
            "body": "<p>Try aliasing the COUNT(DISTINCT <code>ID<\/code>), then retrieving the alias from the ResultSet. This will be more readable and easier to maintain if you end up adding more logic to the query later.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ResultSet rs = statement.executeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT `id`) as NUM_ROWS FROM `users`\");\n\nint count = -1;\nif(rs.next())\n{\n    count = rs.getInt(\"NUM_ROWS\");\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
